OL,3,CSim-swap fraud rises by 1,000% as
OL,4,Ccriminals exploit two-factor
OL,5,Cauthentication
OL,7,FThe number of sim-swap frauds in the
OL,8,FUK has increased by more than 1,000%,
OL,9,Fas criminals try to exploit the
OL,10,Fincreasing reliance on businesses
OL,11,Fusing two-factor authentication to
OL,12,Fprotect their customers' data.
OL,14,FThe National Fraud Database says it
OL,15,Fhas seen a 1,055% increase in the
OL,16,Fnumber of reports of sim-swap fraud,
OL,17,Frising to almost 3,000 cases in 2024
OL,18,Ffrom just 289 in 2023.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/16
