OL,3,CSim-swap fraud rises by 1,000% as
OL,4,Ccriminals exploit two-factor
OL,5,Cauthentication
OL,7,FFirst, the scammer will need to gain
OL,8,Fsome data on the victim, which will
OL,9,Fusually be through buying hacked
OL,10,Fdatabases or phishing scams.
OL,12,FOnce they have enough data, including
OL,13,Fthe victim's phone number, they will
OL,14,Fcontact the victim's service provider
OL,15,Fand impersonate them.
OL,17,FThe fraudster will then trick the
OL,18,Fprovider into swapping the victim's
OL,19,Fmobile number onto a sim card in the
OL,20,Fthief's possession.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/16
