OL,3,CSim-swap fraud rises by 1,000% as
OL,4,Ccriminals exploit two-factor
OL,5,Cauthentication
OL,7,FThe thief now has access to the
OL,8,Fvictim's phone number, meaning they
OL,9,Fcan use it for outbound calls for
OL,10,Ffurther phishing purposes.
OL,12,FBut most importantly, they can now
OL,13,Freceive calls and texts to that
OL,14,Fnumber, including security checks like
OL,15,Ftwo-factor authentication that are
OL,16,Fused by numerous businesses as an
OL,17,Fextra layer of protection.
OL,19,FWith this, the fraudsters will be able
OL,20,Fto access many aspects of the victim's
OL,21,Flife.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/16
