OL,3,CSim-swap fraud rises by 1,000% as
OL,4,Ccriminals exploit two-factor
OL,5,Cauthentication
OL,7,FSecond, turn on two-factor
OL,8,Fauthentication. While sim-swapping
OL,9,Ffraud can specifically get around SMS-
OL,10,Fbased two-stage authentication, if it
OL,11,Fwas not already active on your
OL,12,Faccount, then the fraudster would have
OL,13,Fan even easier time accessing it.
OL,15,FYou can also use several security apps
OL,16,Fto carry out the authentication, which
OL,17,Fdoes not rely on a mobile number and
OL,18,Fis what Which? recommends.
OL,20,FThird, reduce information on your
OL,21,Fsocial media profiles.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/16
